1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,440
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:04,440
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:08,400
My name is Catherine and today we have an intermediate level lesson about going to the
我是Catherine，今天我们有一节中级课程，主题是去

4
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:09,400
bank.
银行。

5
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:10,400
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:13,240
Today we're going to go to the bank and we need to do something there.
今天我们要去银行，而且需要在那里办点事。

7
00:00:13,240 --> 00:00:15,240
We're not going to put money in the bank actually.
实际上，我们不是去存钱。

8
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:16,800
We're going to make a transfer.
我们要办理转账。

9
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:19,960
Okay, so you'll learn all about this in a minute.
好的，你马上就会了解这一切。

10
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:28,160
Let's take a listen to the dialogue first.
我们先来听一下对话。

11
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:29,160
Good morning.
早上好。

12
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:31,080
Welcome to Bank of the USA.
欢迎来到美国银行。

13
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:32,080
How may I help you today?
今天我能为您做些什么？

14
00:00:32,080 --> 00:00:35,280
Hi, I need to transfer some money to another account.
你好，我需要转一些钱到另一个账户。

15
00:00:35,280 --> 00:00:36,280
It's urgent.
很紧急。

16
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:37,280
Okay.
好的。

17
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:39,280
Have you made a wire transfer at our bank before?
您以前在我们银行办理过电汇吗？

18
00:00:39,280 --> 00:00:42,500
No, I've never made a transfer before.
没有，我以前从未办理过转账。

19
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:43,500
It's all right.
没关系。

20
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:45,120
I will take you through the procedure.
我会带您走完整个流程。

21
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:48,920
Are you transferring funds to a company or an individual account?
您是要转账给公司账户还是个人账户？

22
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:49,920
A company account.
公司账户。

23
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:51,520
I need to pay a bill.
我需要付一笔账单。

24
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:52,520
Okay.
好的。

25
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:57,040
I'll need the name of the company and their bank routing number as well as their bank's
我需要公司的名称、他们的银行路由号码，以及他们银行的

26
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:59,080
address and phone number.
地址和电话号码。

27
00:00:59,080 --> 00:01:01,680
I have all the information in this folder.
所有信息都在这个文件夹里。

28
00:01:01,680 --> 00:01:07,840
Well, you've come prepared.
嗯，您准备得很充分。

29
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:12,960
I have all the necessary materials so we can go ahead and make the transfer right now.
我所有必需的材料都带齐了，我们现在就可以进行转账。

30
00:01:12,960 --> 00:01:16,320
It's a simple transaction and we can process it today.
这是一笔简单的交易，我们今天就能处理。

31
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:18,840
Oh, that's such a relief.
哦，那真是太好了。

32
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:20,800
I didn't want the payment to be overdue.
我不想让这笔付款逾期。

33
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:22,260
Thank you so much.
非常感谢。

34
00:01:22,260 --> 00:01:23,260
It's my pleasure.
不客气。

35
00:01:23,260 --> 00:01:27,960
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

36
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:30,720
So interesting dialogue, very common situation.
这段对话很有趣，是非常常见的情况。

37
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:33,480
We need to transfer money to another account.
我们需要把钱转到另一个账户。

38
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:35,760
So we have some very interesting vocab words right there.
所以这里面有一些很有意思的词汇。

39
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:40,640
Why don't we take a look at those on Language Takeaway.
我们不如在“语言要点”部分看看这些词。

40
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:42,880
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

41
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:46,360
So Marco, the first word is one that you've already said a couple of times in today's
那么马可，第一个词是你今天在课程中已经说过几次的。

42
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:47,360
lesson.
课程。

43
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:48,360
It is to transfer.
就是“转账”。

44
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:49,360
Okay, that's right.
没错，就是这样。

45
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:51,100
We need to transfer money.
我们需要转账。

46
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:53,740
So to transfer, what does this verb mean?
那么“转账”这个动词是什么意思呢？

47
00:01:53,740 --> 00:01:57,040
So to transfer means to move from one place to another.
“转账”的意思是从一个地方移动到另一个地方。

48
00:01:57,040 --> 00:02:01,960
In the case of money, you're moving money from one bank to another bank or from one
在钱的情况下，就是把钱从一个银行移动到另一个银行，或者从一个

49
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:03,520
account to another account.
账户移动到另一个账户。

50
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:06,240
So just think of transferring as moving.
所以就把“转账”想象成“移动”就行了。

51
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:07,240
That's right.
没错。

52
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:10,880
But the bank teller also mentioned something about a wire transfer.
但银行柜员还提到了“电汇”。

53
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:13,000
So that's basically the same thing, right?
那基本上是一回事，对吧？

54
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,000
That's right.
没错。

55
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,040
So when you're talking about money, you don't actually take a bag of money and you don't
所以当谈到钱时，你实际上不会拿着一袋钱

56
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:19,600
walk to another bank to put it in the account.
走到另一家银行去存进账户。

57
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:22,760
A wire transfer means that the transfer is electronic.
“电汇”意味着转账是电子的。

58
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:26,820
One bank tells another bank that you're going to exchange this money.
一家银行告诉另一家银行你要交换这笔钱。

59
00:02:26,820 --> 00:02:31,000
So it's going to move from one person to another person or from one company to another company.
所以它会从一个人转移到另一个人，或者从一家公司转移到另一家公司。

60
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,800
But it's never actually the money itself.
但实际的钱本身从未移动过。

61
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:35,720
It's always just the number of funds in the account.
账户里的资金数量总是关键。

62
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:36,720
That's right.
没错。

63
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:42,100
Okay, so a wire transfer, to transfer money electronically from one account to another.
好的，电汇就是通过电子方式将资金从一个账户转移到另一个账户。

64
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:46,280
And talking about this word account, we're talking about a bank account.
说到“账户”这个词，我们指的是银行账户。

65
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:47,280
What is this?
这是什么？

66
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:51,360
Well, this is really important even if you're not making a wire transfer or if you're not
嗯，这真的很重要，即使你不进行电汇或者不在银行工作。

67
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:52,520
working at a bank.
即使不在银行工作。

68
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:56,200
This is something that most people have for their personal use.
这是大多数人个人使用的东西。

69
00:02:56,200 --> 00:03:01,100
So an account is a space for money in a bank that's kind of registered to one person or
所以，账户是银行里一个存放资金的空间，通常登记在一个人或一家公司名下。

70
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,280
one company.
或者一家公司名下。

71
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:04,920
And there are many, many different kinds of accounts.
而且有很多很多不同类型的账户。

72
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:05,920
That's right.
没错。

73
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:07,880
Many of you probably have a savings account.
你们很多人可能都有一个储蓄账户。

74
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:11,240
This is where you keep your money to save for the future.
这是你存钱以备未来之需的地方。

75
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:16,840
Or many companies or people have a checking account or a default account where basically
或者很多公司或个人有一个支票账户或默认账户，基本上你往里面存钱，

76
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:20,560
you put money in, but you're also taking money out and paying for bills and paying to go
同时也会取钱来支付账单、看电影等。

77
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:21,880
to the movies, etc.
等等。

78
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:24,640
Yeah, so these different accounts have different rules.
是的，这些不同的账户有不同的规则。

79
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:28,440
They have rules about how much money you can keep in them or how much money you need to
它们有关于你能存多少钱或需要多少钱才能开户的规则。

80
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:29,600
open them.
才能开户。

81
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:31,600
So the basic word here is account.
所以这里的基本词是 account。

82
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:35,440
And just remember that companies and people can all have accounts at a bank.
记住，公司和人都可以在银行拥有账户。

83
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:36,440
That's right.
没错。

84
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:40,440
Okay, so when talking about an account, we're talking about transferring money to another
好的，所以当我们谈论账户时，我们是在说将钱转移到另一个

85
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:41,440
account.
账户。

86
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:42,920
We don't say we want to transfer money.
我们不会说“转移钱”。

87
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:45,200
We say we want to transfer funds.
我们说“转移资金”。

88
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,600
Funds.
资金。

89
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:51,240
So funds, we usually say in the plural, funds, with an S. This means money.
所以 funds，我们通常用复数形式，funds，加 S。这表示钱。

90
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:55,720
So we're talking about transferring funds from one company to another or I could say
所以我们说的是将资金从一家公司转移到另一家，或者我可以说

91
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:58,040
I need to deposit funds in my account.
我需要往我的账户里存入资金。

92
00:03:58,040 --> 00:03:59,040
That's right.
没错。

93
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:02,840
Now an interesting word because funds with an S at the end, that's a plural noun as you
现在一个有趣的词是 funds，末尾加 S，这是一个复数名词，正如你

94
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:07,740
said, but if we use it in the singular, it could also be a verb, to fund.
所说，但如果用单数形式，它也可以是一个动词，to fund。

95
00:04:07,740 --> 00:04:08,740
That's right.
没错。

96
00:04:08,740 --> 00:04:10,800
And that means to pay for something or someone.
意思是支付某物或某人的费用。

97
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:14,680
So my grandfather funded my college education.
所以我的祖父资助了我的大学教育。

98
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:17,320
He paid money for my college education.
他支付了我大学教育的费用。

99
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:18,320
That's right.
没错。

100
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:22,520
So both words, either the verb or the noun, have to do with money.
所以这两个词，无论是动词还是名词，都与钱有关。

101
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:27,400
And when we're talking about transferring money, we're talking about a type of transaction,
当我们谈论转移钱时，我们是在说一种交易，

102
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,400
right?
对吧？

103
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:32,800
Where a bank transfer or a wire transfer is a type of transaction.
银行转账或电汇是一种交易类型。

104
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:33,800
That's right.
没错。

105
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:38,840
So a transaction is a noun and it's something that you do at a bank, for example, usually
所以 transaction 是一个名词，是你在银行做的事情，例如，通常

106
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:41,940
involving the exchange of money.
涉及金钱交换。

107
00:04:41,940 --> 00:04:48,180
So a wire transfer is a kind of transaction, but also depositing or putting money into
所以电汇是一种交易，但存入或把钱放进

108
00:04:48,180 --> 00:04:50,800
my savings account is also a kind of transaction.
我的储蓄账户也是一种交易。

109
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,800
That's right.
没错。

110
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:55,920
So a transaction is kind of like a business move or a business deal involving money.
所以 transaction 有点像一种商业动作或涉及金钱的商业交易。

111
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:59,880
For example, a transaction can also be buying a car.
例如，交易也可以是买车。

112
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:00,880
That's right.
没错。

113
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:05,800
So the transaction is I give my money to Marco, the car salesperson, and the transaction is
所以交易是我把钱给 Marco，汽车销售员，交易是

114
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,680
exchanging that money for the car.
用钱交换那辆车。

115
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:08,680
That's right.
没错。

116
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:09,680
Okay.
好的。

117
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:14,600
And lastly, since we needed to pay a bill, we were worried that the bill will be overdue
最后，因为我们需要付账单，我们担心账单会逾期，

118
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:17,320
and that's why we really needed to make this wire transfer.
这就是为什么我们真的需要做这笔电汇。

119
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,320
Okay.
好的。

120
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:21,320
So to be overdue is to be late.
所以 overdue 意思是迟了。

121
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:22,320
So think about due.
想想 due。

122
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:25,240
This is the time when something has to be done by.
这是某件事必须完成的截止时间。

123
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:31,960
So for example, if the bill for the electricity is due on Wednesday, but I pay it on Thursday,
例如，如果电费账单在星期三到期，但我星期四才付，

124
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:32,960
it's overdue.
它就逾期了。

125
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:33,960
Okay.
好的。

126
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:37,840
So it not only has to do with money, it could also be something that is late.
所以它不仅与钱有关，也可以指某件事迟了。

127
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:43,000
For example, if I visit my grandma after not going there for three months, you would say
例如，如果我三个月没去看奶奶，然后去看她，你会说

128
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,120
this visit is long overdue.
这次拜访早就该做了。

129
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:49,520
That means Marco should have visited his grandmother earlier, but he didn't.
意思是 Marco 应该早点去看他奶奶，但他没去。

130
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,520
That's right.
没错。

131
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:51,520
Okay.
好的。

132
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:55,440
So a lot of great vocab there all involving banks and different types of words you may
所以这里有很多很棒的词汇，都与银行有关，以及你在

133
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:57,600
find when transferring funds.
转账资金时可能遇到的不同类型的词。

134
00:05:57,600 --> 00:06:09,040
So why don't we listen to the dialogue again and we'll be back in a bit with Fluency Builder.
那我们再听一遍对话，稍后回来进行流利度训练。

135
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,040
Good morning.
早上好。

136
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:12,000
Welcome to Bank of the USA.
欢迎来到美国银行。

137
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,000
How may I help you today?
今天我能为您做什么？

138
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,000
Hi.
你好。

139
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,200
I'm here to transfer some money to another account.
我来这里是为了转一些钱到另一个账户。

140
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:17,200
It's urgent.
很紧急。

141
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,200
Okay.
好的。

142
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:20,240
Have you made a wire transfer at our bank before?
您以前在我们银行做过电汇吗？

143
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:23,400
No, I've never made a transfer before.
没有，我以前从未做过转账。

144
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,400
It's all right.
没关系。

145
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:26,040
I will take you through the procedure.
我会带您走完整个流程。

146
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:29,840
Are you transferring funds to a company or an individual account?
您是要转账给公司还是个人账户？

147
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:30,840
A company account.
公司账户。

148
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,440
I need to pay a bill.
我需要付一笔账单。

149
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:33,440
Okay.
好的。

150
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:37,960
I'll need the name of the company and their bank routing number, as well as their bank's
我需要公司名称和他们的银行路由号码，以及他们银行的

151
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:40,000
address and phone number.
地址和电话号码。

152
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,560
I have all the information in this folder.
所有信息都在这个文件夹里。

153
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:48,760
Well, you've come prepared.
嗯，您准备得很充分。

154
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:53,920
I have all the necessary materials so we can go ahead and make the transfer right now.
我有所有必要的材料，所以我们现在就可以进行转账。

155
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:57,280
It's a simple transaction and we can process it today.
这是一个简单的交易，我们今天就能处理。

156
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:59,760
Oh, that's such a relief.
哦，那真是松了一口气。

157
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:01,760
I didn't want the payment to be overdue.
我不想付款逾期。

158
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:03,200
Thank you so much.
非常感谢。

159
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,200
It's my pleasure.
这是我的荣幸。

160
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,200
All right.
好的。

161
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:06,200
We're back.
我们回来了。

162
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:10,120
So we have three key phrases for you.
所以我们为你准备了三个关键短语。

163
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:13,880
Let's take a look at those now on Fluency Builder.
现在让我们在 Fluency Builder 中看看这些内容。

164
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:15,480
Fluency Builder.
流利度训练。

165
